  "prompt": "How do I get Pikachu as my first Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In **Pok\u00e9mon GO**, you cannot directly choose Pikachu as your first Pok\u00e9mon when you start the game. However, there is a trick to make Pikachu appear as one of your starter Pok\u00e9mon options. Here\u2019s how:\n\n1. **Start the Game**: After creating your character and reaching the point where Professor Willow introduces you to your first Pok\u00e9mon, you\u2019ll see the three classic starters: **Bulbasaur**, **Charmander**, and **Squirtle**.\n\n2. **Ignore the Starters**: Instead of tapping on one of the three starters, walk away from them. They will spawn in the map around you, but don\u2019t tap them.\n\n3. **Keep Walking Away**: Continue walking away from the starters. Each time you do, they will respawn near you. After you\u2019ve walked away **five times**, Pikachu will appear as the fourth starter option alongside the original three.\n\n4. **Catch Pikachu**: Tap on Pikachu and catch it to make it your first Pok\u00e9mon.\n\nThis method allows you to start your journey in **Pok\u00e9mon GO** with Pikachu instead of the traditional starters. Enjoy your adventure with the iconic electric Pok\u00e9mon! \u26a1",
